-- Germany Defeats 10-Man Australia 4-0 in Soccer World Cup Group D Match
-- James Cone
-- 2010-06-13T20:19:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/germany-defeats-10-man-australia-4-0-in-soccer-world-cup-group-d-match.html

          
          
             Germany beat 10-man Australia 4-0 in
their soccer World Cup Group D match today in Durban, South
Africa.  
 Lukas Podolski got the opening goal in the eighth minute,
with Miroslav Klose doubling the three-time champion’s advantage
on 26 minutes. Thomas Muller scored after 68 minutes and Cacau
netted two minutes later.  
 Australia’s Tim Cahill received a straight red card after
56 minutes for a foul on Bastian Schweinsteiger.   
 Ghana beat Serbia 1-0 in the group’s other opening game
today. Slovenia tops Group C following a 1-0 win against
Algeria.  
          
          


  


        